## PRIME DIRECTIVE

> **Rules govern agents. Agents enforce rules. Community evolves rules.**
> **NEVER write manual logic if a Tool (MCP) or Agent exists.**
> **CHALLENGE before EXECUTE. Process before code.**
> **DRY-RUN FIRST. Always.**

## ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (MANDATORY)

> **Every message follows:** INTAKE -> CHALLENGE -> PLAN -> GATE -> EXECUTE -> VERIFY -> LEARN
> **Full spec:** `.guarani/orchestration/PIPELINE.md`

| Complexity | Pipeline Depth | Min Thoughts |
|------------|---------------|---------------|
| TRIVIAL | Skip to Execute | 0 |
| SIMPLE | Intake + Plan + Execute | 0 |
| MODERATE | Full pipeline, questions mandatory | 3 |
| COMPLEX | Full pipeline + Sequential Thinking | 5 |
| CRITICAL | Full pipeline + user approval | 7 |

## MANDAMENTOS

1. **CHALLENGE** тАФ Question, detect contradictions, ask for evidence.
2. **ONE THING** тАФ Each agent does ONE thing. Each module solves ONE problem.
3. **ZERO DEPS** тАФ Agents use only Node/Bun stdlib. No framework dependencies.
4. **DRY-RUN FIRST** тАФ Every agent SHALL support `--dry` before `--exec`.
5. **REGISTRY** тАФ No agent runs without `agents/registry/agents.json` entry.
6. **COST** тАФ AI calls use `packages/shared/src/llm-provider.ts`. Cost tracked.
7. **SHARED** тАФ Reusable code goes in `packages/shared/`. Zero duplication.
8. **COMMIT** тАФ Conventional commits every 30-60min.
9. **SCOPE** тАФ Do ONLY what was asked. ASK before creating new features.
10. **TEACH** тАФ Explain WHY, not just WHAT. Question bad ideas.
11. **EDIT SIZE** тАФ Max 80 lines per write_to_file/edit call.
12. **FROZEN** тАФ Never edit frozen zones without explicit user approval + proof.
13. **CODEX** тАФ Use Codex for diff-heavy, audit, and mechanical work.
14. **HUMAN LOOP** тАФ For ambiguous decisions, ask before acting.
15. **PROPAGATE** тАФ Kernel governance/workflow changes are not complete until `bun run governance:sync:exec` passes and `bun run governance:check` returns 0 drift.
16. **FOCUS** тАФ Do NOT reinvent what exists (generic scanners, linters, dep auditors). EGOS's moat is governance-as-code, Brazilian compliance, and orchestration. Before creating any new agent, search existing marketplaces (OpenClaw, aregistry.ai, Composio, npm). If user proposes new scope, acknowledge it, log to TASKS.md backlog, but REMIND them of current mission focus.
17. **REAL TESTS** тАФ No capability is "validated" by string-matching grep. Every shared module MUST have `bun test` coverage with real data. A compliance score without behavioral tests is paperwork, not proof.
18. **NO CIRCULAR VALIDATION** тАФ Agents that check for their own outputs are not tests. Validation requires external confrontation: real PII, adversarial prompts, actual API calls, or user-verified results.

